(2m+3)x^2 + (4m-2)x - (m+1) = 0
a=2m+3
b=4m-2
c=-m-1
x_1x_2=1,
m
m
 ax^2+bx+c=0, 
 x_1=\frac{-b+\sqrt{b^2-4ac}}{2a}, 
 x_2=\frac{-b-\sqrt{b^2-4ac}}{2a}. 
 \frac{-b+\sqrt{b^2-4ac}}{-b-\sqrt{b^2-4ac}}=1, 
 -b+\sqrt{b^2-4ac}=-b-\sqrt{b^2-4ac}, 
 +\sqrt{b^2-4ac}=-\sqrt{b^2-4ac}, 
 \sqrt{b^2-4ac}=0, 
 b^2-4ac=0, 
 b=\pm 2\sqrt{ac}. 
 4m-2=\pm2\sqrt{-(m+1)(2m+3)}. 
